'''''Queen of the Valkyries''''' was a [[Yevetha]]n [[Aramadia-class thrustship|''Aramadia''-class thrustship]].

==History==
As part of his deal to aid [[Nil Spaar]]'s efforts against the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], [[Belezaboth Ourn]] allowed the [[Paqwe]] diplomatic vessel ''[[Mother's Valkyrie]]'' to be damaged by the departing [[Aramadia (Aramadia-class)|''Aramadia'']]. In exchange, Ourn was promised ''Queen of the Valkyries'', likely known by a Yevethan name at the time.

When the [[New Republic Fifth Fleet|New Republic Fifth Battle Group]] entered the [[Farlax sector/Legends|Farlax sector]], Nil Spaar rescinded his offer and kept ''Queen'' in the [[Koornacht Cluster/Legends|Koornacht Cluster]] for defense, with the added benefit of stranding Ourn on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] to act as his spy.

